For each gene set, gene expressions are simulated from MVN(ΜG, ΣG) where ΜG is the mean vector of gene expressions, taken from a truncated exponential distribution with λ = 0.7. ΣG is the variance-covariance matrix of genes within a gene set. The variances of the genes were set at \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
